  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Cook",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></h2><h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>Experienced and disciplined <strong>Senior Cook</strong> with strong expertise in authentic Indian cuisine, specializing in traditional and contemporary <strong>South Indian dishes</strong>. Responsible for daily food preparation and cooking, ensuring consistent taste, quality, hygiene, and smooth kitchen operations while supporting the Head Chef / Executive Chef.<br /></p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p><ul><li>Prepare and cook menu items according to standard recipes and instructions from senior chefs.</li><li>Ensure consistency in taste, quality, presentation, and portion control.</li><li>Handle daily food preparation, cooking, and service during regular and peak hours.</li><li>Supervise and guide junior cooks and kitchen assistants when required.</li><li>Maintain high standards of food hygiene, cleanliness, and safety at all times.</li><li>Follow food safety regulations and company SOPs.</li><li>Assist with inventory control, stock rotation (FIFO), and minimizing food wastage.</li><li>Maintain cleanliness of kitchen equipment, workstations, and storage areas.</li><li>Report any equipment issues, shortages, or food quality concerns to the Head Chef.</li><li>Work efficiently under pressure in a fast-paced kitchen environment.</li><li>Support audits, inspections, and quality checks when required.<br /><br /><strong>Skills </strong><br /></li><li>Strong cooking skills with good knowledge of kitchen operations.</li><li>Ability to follow recipes, instructions, and kitchen procedures accurately.</li><li>Good time management and multitasking abilities.Leadership skills to guide junior staff when needed.</li><li>Understanding of food hygiene, safety, and sanitation standards.</li><li>Physically fit and able to work long hours and shifts.</li><li>Reliable, disciplined, and a strong team player.</li></ul></p><p><br /><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>3–7 years</strong> of relevant experience as a Cook or Senior Cook.</p></li><li><p>Formal culinary training or equivalent practical experience preferred..</p></li><li><p>Experience in restaurants, hotels, catering, or institutional kitchens preferred.</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in a multicultural and fast-paced environment.</p></li></ul>",
